15/11/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament started debating a draft resolution Monday (14 November) on combating corruption, discussing proposals for the text submitted by the ruling Democratic Party (DP) and the main opposition Socialist Party. 
The opposition accuses the DP of using the corruption problem as a pretext for putting political pressure on some state institutions, including the general prosecutor's office.
In other news, Monday, Germany announced that it is loaning 7.6m euros to Albania to help the country repair the water supply and sewage systems in the tourist resort of Lake Ohrid in Pogradeca.
Also Monday, the European Commission said it has given Albania 3.6m euros to build a new prison, in Korce. 
The facility will house 350 inmates. 
(Albanian News - 15/11/05; AP - 14/11/05)
